The paper proposes a framework for dimensionality reduction using Riemannian optimization on the Grassmann manifold. This involves modeling similarity/dissimilarity between subspaces using various metrics defined on the Grassmannian and formulating dimensionality reduction as a non-linear constraint optimization problem. The paper also discusses the components required for Riemannian optimization and how they can be derived from the original Grassmannian. Given these topics, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could place it in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
